solution:
Let $x, y, z$ be the hours machine X, Y, and Z should operate, respectively. We have the system of equations: 
5x + 4y + 2z = 19 \quad 	ext{(Type A gadgets)}
3x + 7y + 4z = 29 \quad 	ext{(Type B gadgets)}
	ext{and } x + y + z = 6 \quad 	ext{(Total hours)}.
We need to solve this system to find the values of $x, y,$ and $z$. Using methods of substitution or elimination to solve these equations will yield the required hours of operation for each machine.  oxed{1}
